@page "/documentation"

<PageTitle>Documentation - grow.IT</PageTitle>

<div class="documentation-page">
    <PageHeader Title="Documentation" Subtitle="A plain-language guide to what Grow.IT does, where information goes, and how to use the workspace." />

    <section class="doc-hero card-growit">
        <div class="card-body">
            <div class="doc-hero-copy">
                <span class="doc-kicker">Start Here</span>
                <h2>Grow.IT helps you turn what your organization already knows into usable proof.</h2>
                <p>
                    The platform saves your organization details, people served, programs, money sources, service costs,
                    follow-ups, outcomes, documents, and reports in one place. That information can then support funding
                    conversations, board updates, donor reports, ASC readiness, and your organization portfolio.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="doc-flow" aria-label="Grow.IT workflow">
                <div><strong>1</strong><span>Save data</span></div>
                <i class="bi bi-arrow-right"></i>
                <div><strong>2</strong><span>Track work</span></div>
                <i class="bi bi-arrow-right"></i>
                <div><strong>3</strong><span>Generate proof</span></div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="doc-section">
        <h2 class="section-title">What Grow.IT Is</h2>
        <div class="doc-card-grid">
            <article class="doc-card">
                <i class="bi bi-database-check"></i>
                <h3>Organization Database</h3>
                <p>Save the information your team normally keeps in notes, spreadsheets, inboxes, and memory.</p>
            </article>
            <article class="doc-card">
                <i class="bi bi-cash-stack"></i>
                <h3>Service Cost Tracker</h3>
                <p>Connect people, programs, money sources, and support provided so you can show the dollar value of your work.</p>
            </article>
            <article class="doc-card">
                <i class="bi bi-patch-check"></i>
                <h3>Readiness Guide</h3>
                <p>Use ASC to see what is complete, what is missing, and what needs to improve before bigger funding conversations.</p>
            </article>
            <article class="doc-card">
                <i class="bi bi-file-earmark-bar-graph"></i>
                <h3>Reporting Workspace</h3>
                <p>Turn saved data into reports you can review, export, and reuse instead of recreating everything by hand.</p>
            </article>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="doc-section">
        <h2 class="section-title">Recommended Workflow</h2>
        <div class="doc-steps">
            <article>
                <span>Step 1</span>
                <h3>Set up the organization</h3>
                <p>Go to Settings and complete the organization profile, contact details, team access, and basic operating information.</p>
                <a href="/settings">Open Settings</a>
            </article>
            <article>
                <span>Step 2</span>
                <h3>Add people and households</h3>
                <p>Use People and Households to save who you serve. This becomes the base for service records and impact reporting.</p>
                <a href="/clients">Open People</a>
            </article>
            <article>
                <span>Step 3</span>
                <h3>Define programs and money sources</h3>
                <p>Add your programs, usual service costs, grants, donations, budgets, or other money sources.</p>
                <a href="/programs">Open Programs</a>
            </article>
            <article>
                <span>Step 4</span>
                <h3>Record services provided</h3>
                <p>Use Service Records to show what support was provided, who received it, what it cost, and what funded it.</p>
                <a href="/investments">Open Service Records</a>
            </article>
            <article>
                <span>Step 5</span>
                <h3>Track follow-ups and outcomes</h3>
                <p>Use Follow-ups for next steps and Outcomes for proof that something changed or was completed.</p>
                <a href="/tasks">Open Follow-ups</a>
            </article>
            <article>
                <span>Step 6</span>
                <h3>Review ASC and generate reports</h3>
                <p>Check your ASC Score, then generate reports for funders, donors, board members, and internal planning.</p>
                <a href="/organization">Open ASC Score</a>
            </article>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="doc-section">
        <h2 class="section-title">Page Guide</h2>
        <div class="doc-table-wrap card-growit">
            <table class="doc-table">
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Page</th>
                        <th>Use it for</th>
                        <th>Why it matters</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr>
                        <td><a href="/home">Dashboard</a></td>
                        <td>See saved data, next steps, recent activity, and service value.</td>
                        <td>Gives a quick picture of what is happening right now.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><a href="/clients">People</a></td>
                        <td>Save profiles for people your organization serves.</td>
                        <td>Connects services, costs, outcomes, and reports to real people.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><a href="/households">Households</a></td>
                        <td>Group people together by household.</td>
                        <td>Helps explain family context and household-level support.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><a href="/programs">Programs</a></td>
                        <td>Define services, capacity, descriptions, and usual cost per service.</td>
                        <td>Shows what your organization does and what it costs to deliver.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><a href="/funds">Money Sources</a></td>
                        <td>Save grants, donations, budgets, restricted funds, or other available money.</td>
                        <td>Shows where support is funded from and how much is left.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><a href="/investments">Service Records</a></td>
                        <td>Record support provided, cost, program, money source, and person served.</td>
                        <td>This is where Grow.IT shows the dollar value of help delivered.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><a href="/imprints">Outcomes</a></td>
                        <td>Save milestones, changes, proof, and impact notes.</td>
                        <td>Turns work performed into impact evidence.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><a href="/tasks">Follow-ups</a></td>
                        <td>Assign next steps, document collection, board items, program tasks, and client follow-ups.</td>
                        <td>Shows operational follow-through for ASC and internal accountability.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><a href="/documents">Documents</a></td>
                        <td>Save file links and records connected to clients and organizational records.</td>
                        <td>Keeps proof close to the data it supports.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><a href="/organization">ASC Score</a></td>
                        <td>Review Accountability, Stability & Capacity progress.</td>
                        <td>Shows readiness based on saved data, not guesses.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><a href="/reports">Reports</a></td>
                        <td>Generate, review, download, and schedule reports.</td>
                        <td>Turns platform data into funder, donor, board, and planning documents.</td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="doc-section">
        <h2 class="section-title">How ASC Uses Your Data</h2>
        <div class="doc-split">
            <div class="doc-panel">
                <h3>ASC is earned from saved evidence.</h3>
                <p>
                    The score looks at organization profile completion, active users, people served, programs, money sources,
                    service records, outcomes, documents, reports, follow-ups, and operating history.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="doc-panel">
                <h3>To improve the score, add stronger proof.</h3>
                <p>
                    Complete the basics first, then add documents, record service costs, close follow-ups, track outcomes,
                    generate reports, and keep activity consistent over time.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="doc-section">
        <h2 class="section-title">Demo Walkthrough</h2>
        <div class="doc-checklist card-growit">
            <div class="card-body">
                <ol>
                    <li>Open the Dashboard and point out monthly service value and next steps.</li>
                    <li>Open People and show how a person or household becomes the center of service history.</li>
                    <li>Open Programs and Money Sources to show how services and funding are structured.</li>
                    <li>Open Service Records and show the dollar value tied to support provided.</li>
                    <li>Open Outcomes to show proof, milestones, and impact evidence.</li>
                    <li>Open Follow-ups to show who owns the next step and whether work was completed.</li>
                    <li>Open ASC Score to show readiness progress and missing items.</li>
                    <li>Open Reports and generate an impact or service cost report.</li>
                </ol>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</div>
